# v0.5.11 Change Log

**Theme**: Type safety hardening — systematic MyPy error elimination across the `aitbc/` shared core library, duplicate route audit, and systemd symlink repair.

**Goal**: Achieve 0 MyPy errors across all non-excluded files in `aitbc/`, fix all Ruff lint issues, migrate deprecated `TypeAlias` syntax, remove duplicate route registrations in coordinator-api, and repair the broken `aitbc-recovery` systemd symlink.

**Context**: v0.5.10 implemented the compute-seconds unit system (1 AIT = 3600 seconds). v0.5.11 focuses on code quality and type safety: eliminating implicit Optional bugs, unreachable code, incorrect attribute access on `None`-typed variables, redundant `.json()` calls on already-parsed dicts, and missing type annotations across 20+ files in the shared core library.

**Status**: Fully implemented. All 17 planned items are complete.

